actively_involved_in.description: holds between a continuant and a process or function, where the continuant actively contributes to part or all of the process or function it realizes

affects.description: describes an entity that has a direct affect on the state or quality of another existing entity. Use of the 'affects' predicate implies that the affected entity already exists, unlike predicates such as 'affects risk for' and 'prevents, where the outcome is something that may or may not come to be.

affects_abundance_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one changes the amount of the other within a system of interest

affects_activity_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one changes the activity of the other within a system of interest

affects_degradation_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one impacts the rate of degradation of the other within a system of interest

affects_expression_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one changes the level of expression of the other within a system of interest

affects_folding_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one changes the rate or quality of folding of the other

affects_localization_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one changes the localization of the other within a system of interest

affects_metabolic_processing_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one impacts the metabolic processing of the other within a system of interest

affects_molecular_modification_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one leads changes in the molecular modification(s) of the other (e.g. via post-translational modifications of proteins such as the addition of phosphoryl group, or via redox reaction that adds or subtracts electrons)

affects_mutation_rate_of.description: holds between a molecular entity and a genomic entity where the action or effect of the molecular entity impacts the rate of mutation of the genomic entity within a system of interest

affects_response_to.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one impacts the susceptibility of a biological entity or system (e.g. an organism, cell, cellular component, macromolecular machine, biological or pathological process) to the other

affects_risk_for.description: holds between two entities where exposure to one entity alters the chance of developing the other

affects_secretion_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one impacts the rate of secretion of the other out of a cell, gland, or organ

affects_splicing_of.description: holds between a molecular entity and an mRNA where the action or effect of the molecular entity impacts the splicing of the mRNA

affects_stability_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one impacts the stability of the other within a system of interest

affects_synthesis_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one impacts the rate of chemical synthesis of the other

affects_transport_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one impacts the rate of transport of the other across some boundary in a system of interest

affects_uptake_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one impacts the rate of uptake of the other into of a cell, gland, or organ

association_slot.description: any slot that relates an association to another entity

association_type.description: connects an association to the type of association (e.g. gene to phenotype)

biomarker_for.description: holds between a measurable molecular entity and a disease or phenotypic feature, where the entity is used as an indicator of the presence or state of the disease or feature.

capable_of.description: holds between a physical entity and process or function, where the continuant alone has the ability to carry out the process or function.

category.description: Name of the high level ontology class in which this entity is categorized. Corresponds to the label for the biolink entity type class. In a neo4j database this MAY correspond to the neo4j label tag

causes.description: holds between two entities where the occurrence, existence, or activity of one causes the occurrence or  generation of the other

change_is_catalyzed_by.description: hyperedge connecting an association between two causally connected entities (for example, two chemical entities, or a chemical entity in that changes location) and the gene product, gene, or complex that enables or catalyzes the change.

clinical_modifier_qualifier.description: Used to characterize and specify the phenotypic abnormalities defined in the Phenotypic abnormality subontology, with respect to severity, laterality, age of onset, and other aspects

coexists_with.description: holds between two entities that are co-located in the same aggregate object, process, or spatio-temporal region

colocalizes_with.description: holds between two entities that are observed to be located in the same place.

contributes_to.description: holds between two entities where the occurrence, existence, or activity of one causes or contributes to the occurrence or generation of the other

correlated_with.description: holds between a disease or phenotypic feature and a measurable molecular entity that is used as an indicator of the presence or state of the disease or feature.

decreases_activity_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one decreases the activity of the other within a system of interest

decreases_expression_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one decreases the level of expression of the other within a system of interest

decreases_mutation_rate_of.description: holds between a molecular entity and a genomic entity where the action or effect of the molecular entity decreases the rate of mutation of the genomic entity within a system of interest

decreases_stability_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one decreases the stability of the other within a system of interest

decreases_synthesis_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one decreases the rate of chemical synthesis of the other

decreases_transport_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one decreases the rate of transport of the other across some boundary in a system of interest

decreases_uptake_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one decreases the rate of uptake of the other into of a cell, gland, or organ

derives_into.description: holds between two distinct material entities, the old entity and the new entity, in which the new entity begins to exist when the old entity ceases to exist, and the new entity inherits the significant portion of the matter of the old entity

description.description: a human-readable description of a thing

disrupts.description: describes a relationship where one entity degrades or interferes with the structure, function, or occurrence of another.

edge_label.description: A high-level grouping for the relationship type. AKA minimal predicate. This is analogous to category for nodes.

enabled_by.description: holds between a process and a physical entity, where the physical entity executes the process

expressed_in.description: holds between a gene or gene product and an anatomical entity in which it is expressed

expresses.description: holds between an anatomical entity and gene or gene product that is expressed there

filler.description: The value in a property-value tuple

frequency_qualifier.description: a qualifier used in a phenotypic association to state how frequent the phenotype is observed in the subject

full_name.description: a long-form human readable name for a thing

gene_associated_with_condition.description: holds between a gene and a disease or phenotypic feature that the gene or its alleles/products may influence, contribute to, or correlate with

genetically_interacts_with.description: holds between two genes whose phenotypic effects are dependent on each other in some way - such that their combined phenotypic effects are the result of some interaction between the activity of their gene products. Examples include epistasis and synthetic lethality.

has_attribute_type.description: connects an attribute to a class that describes it

has_biological_sequence.description: connects a genomic feature to its sequence

has_biomarker.description: holds between a disease or phenotypic feature and a measurable molecular entity that is used as an indicator of the presence or state of the disease or feature.

has_chemical_formula.description: description of chemical compound based on element symbols

has_confidence_level.description: connects an association to a qualitative term denoting the level of confidence

has_count.description: number of things with a particular property

has_gene_product.description: holds between a gene and a transcribed and/or translated product generated from it

has_molecular_consequence.description: connects a sequence variant to a class describing the molecular consequence. E.g.  SO:0001583

has_numeric_value.description: connects a quantity value to a number

has_output.description: holds between a process and a continuant, where the continuant is an output of the process

has_part.description: holds between wholes and their parts (material entities or processes)

has_participant.description: holds between a process and a continuant, where the continuant is somehow involved in the process

has_percentage.description: equivalent to has quotient multiplied by 100

has_quantitative_value.description: connects an attribute to a value

has_total.description: total number of things in a particular reference set

ChemicalToChemicalDerivationAssociation.description:
A causal relationship between two chemical entities, where the subject represents the upstream entity and the object represents the downstream. For any such association there is an implicit reaction:
  IF
  R has-input C1 AND
  R has-output C2 AND
  R enabled-by P AND
  R type Reaction
  THEN
  C1 derives-into C2 <<change is catalyzed by P>>

GeneToGeneHomologyAssociation.description: A homology association between two genes. May be orthology (in which case the species of subject and object should differ) or paralogy (in which case the species may be the same)
GeneToGeneHomologyAssociation.title: GeneToGeneHomologyAssociation

GeneToGeneProductRelationship.description: A gene is transcribed and potentially translated to a gene product
GeneToGeneProductRelationship.title: GeneToGeneProductRelationship

Genome.description: A genome is the sum of genetic material within a cell or virion.
Genome.title: Genome

GenomicEntity.description: an entity that can either be directly located on a genome (gene, transcript, exon, regulatory region) or is encoded in a genome (protein)

has_biological_sequence.description: connects a genomic feature to its sequence

GenomicEntity.title: GenomicEntity

GenomicSequenceLocalization.description: A relationship between a sequence feature and an entity it is localized to. The reference entity may be a chromosome, chromosome region or information entity such as a contig
GenomicSequenceLocalization.title: GenomicSequenceLocalization

Genotype.description: An information content entity that describes a genome by specifying the total variation in genomic sequence and/or gene expression, relative to some extablished background
Genotype.title: Genotype

GenotypeToGeneAssociation.description: Any association between a genotype and a gene. The genotype have have multiple variants in that gene or a single one. There is no assumption of cardinality
GenotypeToGeneAssociation.title: GenotypeToGeneAssociation

GenotypeToGenotypePartAssociation.description: Any association between one genotype and a genotypic entity that is a sub-component of it
GenotypeToGenotypePartAssociation.title: GenotypeToGenotypePartAssociation

GenotypeToPhenotypicFeatureAssociation.description: Any association between one genotype and a phenotypic feature, where having the genotype confers the phenotype, either in isolation or through environment
GenotypeToPhenotypicFeatureAssociation.title: GenotypeToPhenotypicFeatureAssociation

GenotypeToVariantAssociation.description: Any association between a genotype and a sequence variant.
GenotypeToVariantAssociation.title: GenotypeToVariantAssociation

GenotypicSex.description: An attribute corresponding to the genotypic sex of the individual, based upon genotypic composition of sex chromosomes.
GenotypicSex.title: GenotypicSex

GeographicLocation.description: a location that can be described in lat/long coordinates
GeographicLocation.title: GeographicLocation

GeographicLocationAtTime.description: a location that can be described in lat/long coordinates, for a particular time
GeographicLocationAtTime.title: GeographicLocationAtTime

Haplotype.description: A set of zero or more Alleles on a single instance of a Sequence[VMC]
Haplotype.title: Haplotype

in_taxon.description: connects a thing to a class representing a taxon

LifeStage.description: A stage of development or growth of an organism, including post-natal adult stages

in_taxon.description: connects a thing to a class representing a taxon

LifeStage.title: LifeStage

MacromolecularMachine.description: A union of gene, gene product, and macromolecular complex. These are the basic units of function in a cell. They either carry out individual biological activities, or they encode molecules which do this.
MacromolecularMachine.title: MacromolecularMachine

MacromolecularMachineToBiologicalProcess.description: A functional association between a macromolecular machine (gene, gene product or complex) and a biological process or pathway (as represented in the GO biological process branch), where the entity carries out some part of the process, regulates it, or acts upstream of it
MacromolecularMachineToBiologicalProcess.title: MacromolecularMachineToBiologicalProcessAssociation

MacromolecularMachineToCellularComponent.description: A functional association between a macromolecular machine (gene, gene product or complex) and a cellular component (as represented in the GO cellular component branch), where the entity carries out its function in the cellular component
MacromolecularMachineToCellularComponent.title: MacromolecularMachineToCellularComponentAssociation

MacromolecularMachineToMolecularActivity.description: A functional association between a macromolecular machine (gene, gene product or complex) and a molecular activity (as represented in the GO molecular function branch), where the entity carries out the activity, or contributes to its execution
MacromolecularMachineToMolecularActivity.title: MacromolecularMachineToMolecularActivityAssociation

MaterialSample.description: A sample is a limited quantity of something (e.g. an individual or set of individuals from a population, or a portion of a substance) to be used for testing, analysis, inspection, investigation, demonstration, or trial use. [SIO]

has_attribute.description: connects any named thing to an attribute

MaterialSample.title: MaterialSample

MaterialSampleDerivationAssociation.description: An association between a material sample and the material entity it is derived from
MaterialSampleDerivationAssociation.title: MaterialSampleDerivationAssociation

MaterialSampleToDiseaseOrPhenotypicFeatu.description: An association between a material sample and a disease or phenotype
MaterialSampleToDiseaseOrPhenotypicFeatu.title: MaterialSampleToDiseaseOrPhenotypicFeatureAssociation

Metabolite.description: Any intermediate or product resulting from metabolism. Includes primary and secondary metabolites.
Metabolite.title: Metabolite

MolecularActivity.description: An execution of a molecular function carried out by a gene product or macromolecular complex.
MolecularActivity.title: MolecularActivity

MolecularEntity.description: A gene, gene product, small molecule or macromolecule (including protein complex)

affects_abundance_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one changes the amount of the other within a system of interest

affects_activity_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one changes the activity of the other within a system of interest

affects_degradation_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one impacts the rate of degradation of the other within a system of interest

affects_expression_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one changes the level of expression of the other within a system of interest

affects_folding_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one changes the rate or quality of folding of the other

affects_localization_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one changes the localization of the other within a system of interest

affects_metabolic_processing_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one impacts the metabolic processing of the other within a system of interest

affects_molecular_modification_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one leads changes in the molecular modification(s) of the other (e.g. via post-translational modifications of proteins such as the addition of phosphoryl group, or via redox reaction that adds or subtracts electrons)

affects_mutation_rate_of.description: holds between a molecular entity and a genomic entity where the action or effect of the molecular entity impacts the rate of mutation of the genomic entity within a system of interest

affects_response_to.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one impacts the susceptibility of a biological entity or system (e.g. an organism, cell, cellular component, macromolecular machine, biological or pathological process) to the other

affects_secretion_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one impacts the rate of secretion of the other out of a cell, gland, or organ

affects_splicing_of.description: holds between a molecular entity and an mRNA where the action or effect of the molecular entity impacts the splicing of the mRNA

affects_stability_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one impacts the stability of the other within a system of interest

affects_synthesis_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one impacts the rate of chemical synthesis of the other

affects_transport_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one impacts the rate of transport of the other across some boundary in a system of interest

affects_uptake_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one impacts the rate of uptake of the other into of a cell, gland, or organ

biomarker_for.description: holds between a measurable molecular entity and a disease or phenotypic feature, where the entity is used as an indicator of the presence or state of the disease or feature.

decreases_abundance_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one decreases the amount of the other within a system of interest

decreases_activity_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one decreases the activity of the other within a system of interest

decreases_degradation_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one decreases the rate of degradation of the other within a system of interest

decreases_expression_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one decreases the level of expression of the other within a system of interest

decreases_folding_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one decreases the rate or quality of folding of the other

decreases_localization_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one decreases the proper localization of the other within a system of interest

decreases_metabolic_processing_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one decreases the rate of metabolic processing of the other within a system of interest

decreases_molecular_modification_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one leads to decreased molecular modification(s) of the other (e.g. via post-translational modifications of proteins such as the addition of phosphoryl group, or via redox reaction that adds or subtracts electrons)

decreases_mutation_rate_of.description: holds between a molecular entity and a genomic entity where the action or effect of the molecular entity decreases the rate of mutation of the genomic entity within a system of interest

decreases_response_to.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one decreases the susceptibility of a biological entity or system (e.g. an organism, cell, cellular component, macromolecular machine, biological or pathological process) to the other

decreases_secretion_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one decreases the rate of secretion of the other out of a cell, gland, or organ

decreases_splicing_of.description: holds between a molecular entity and an mRNA where the action or effect of the molecular entity decreases the proper splicing of the mRNA

decreases_stability_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one decreases the stability of the other within a system of interest

decreases_synthesis_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one decreases the rate of chemical synthesis of the other

decreases_transport_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one decreases the rate of transport of the other across some boundary in a system of interest

decreases_uptake_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one decreases the rate of uptake of the other into of a cell, gland, or organ

in_taxon.description: connects a thing to a class representing a taxon

increases_abundance_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one increases the amount of the other within a system of interest

increases_activity_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one increases the activity of the other within a system of interest

increases_degradation_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one increases the rate of degradation of the other within a system of interest

increases_expression_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one increases the level of expression of the other within a system of interest

increases_folding_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one increases the rate or quality of folding of the other

increases_localization_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one increases the proper localization of the other within a system of interest

increases_metabolic_processing_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one increases the rate of metabolic processing of the other within a system of interest

increases_molecular_modification_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one leads to increased molecular modification(s) of the other (e.g. via post-translational modifications of proteins such as the addition of phosphoryl group, or via redox reaction that adds or subtracts electrons)

increases_mutation_rate_of.description: holds between a molecular entity and a genomic entity where the action or effect of the molecular entity increases the rate of mutation of the genomic entity within a system of interest

increases_response_to.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one increases the susceptibility of a biological entity or system (e.g. an organism, cell, cellular component, macromolecular machine, biological or pathological process) to the other

increases_secretion_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one increases the rate of secretion of the other out of a cell, gland, or organ

increases_splicing_of.description: holds between a molecular entity and an mRNA where the action or effect of the molecular entity increases the proper splicing of the mRNA

increases_stability_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one increases the stability of the other within a system of interest

increases_synthesis_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one increases the rate of chemical synthesis of the other

increases_transport_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one increases the rate of transport of the other across some boundary in a system of interest

increases_uptake_of.description: holds between two molecular entities where the action or effect of one increases the rate of uptake of the other into of a cell, gland, or organ

MolecularEntity.title: MolecularEntity

actively_involved_in.description: holds between a continuant and a process or function, where the continuant actively contributes to part or all of the process or function it realizes

affects.description: describes an entity that has a direct affect on the state or quality of another existing entity. Use of the 'affects' predicate implies that the affected entity already exists, unlike predicates such as 'affects risk for' and 'prevents, where the outcome is something that may or may not come to be.

affects_risk_for.description: holds between two entities where exposure to one entity alters the chance of developing the other

capable_of.description: holds between a physical entity and process or function, where the continuant alone has the ability to carry out the process or function.

category.description: Name of the high level ontology class in which this entity is categorized. Corresponds to the label for the biolink entity type class. In a neo4j database this MAY correspond to the neo4j label tag

causes.description: holds between two entities where the occurrence, existence, or activity of one causes the occurrence or  generation of the other

coexists_with.description: holds between two entities that are co-located in the same aggregate object, process, or spatio-temporal region

colocalizes_with.description: holds between two entities that are observed to be located in the same place.

contributes_to.description: holds between two entities where the occurrence, existence, or activity of one causes or contributes to the occurrence or generation of the other

creation_date.description: date on which thing was created. This can be applied to nodes or edges

derives_from.description: holds between two distinct material entities, the new entity and the old entity, in which the new entity begins to exist when the old entity ceases to exist, and the new entity inherits the significant portion of the matter of the old entity

derives_into.description: holds between two distinct material entities, the old entity and the new entity, in which the new entity begins to exist when the old entity ceases to exist, and the new entity inherits the significant portion of the matter of the old entity

description.description: a human-readable description of a thing

disrupts.description: describes a relationship where one entity degrades or interferes with the structure, function, or occurrence of another.

filler.description: The value in a property-value tuple

full_name.description: a long-form human readable name for a thing

has_biological_sequence.description: connects a genomic feature to its sequence

has_chemical_formula.description: description of chemical compound based on element symbols

has_count.description: number of things with a particular property

has_gene.description: connects and entity to a single gene

has_molecular_consequence.description: connects a sequence variant to a class describing the molecular consequence. E.g.  SO:0001583

has_part.description: holds between wholes and their parts (material entities or processes)

has_percentage.description: equivalent to has quotient multiplied by 100

has_total.description: total number of things in a particular reference set

homologous_to.description: holds between two biological entities that have common evolutionary origin

id.description: A unique identifier for a thing. Must be either a CURIE shorthand for a URI or a complete URI

interacts_with.description: holds between any two entities that directly or indirectly interact with each other

iri.description: An IRI for the node. This is determined by the id using expansion rules.

located_in.description: holds between a material entity and a material entity or site within which it is located (but of which it is not considered a part)

location_of.description: holds between material entity or site and a material entity that is located within it (but not considered a part of it)

manifestation_of.description: used in SemMedDB for linking things like dysfunctions and processes to some disease or syndrome

model_of.description: holds between an entity and some other entity it approximates for purposes of scientific study, in virtue of its exhibiting similar features of the studied entity.

name.description: A human-readable name for a thing

node_property.description: A grouping for any property that holds between a node and a value

occurs_in.description: holds between a process and a material entity or site within which the process occurs

orthologous_to.description: a homology relationship between entities (typically genes) that diverged after a speciation event.

overlaps.description: holds between entties that overlap in their extents (materials or processes)

paralogous_to.description: a homology relationship that holds between entities (typically genes) that diverged after a duplication event.

part_of.description: holds between parts and wholes (material entities or processes)

participates_in.description: holds between a continuant and a process, where the continuant is somehow involved in the process

physically_interacts_with.description: holds between two entities that make physical contact as part of some interaction

predisposes.description: holds between two entities where exposure to one entity increases the chance of developing the other

prevents.description: holds between an entity whose application or use reduces the likelihood of a potential outcome. Typically used to associate a chemical substance, exposure, activity, or medical intervention that can prevent the onset a disease or phenotypic feature.

produces.description: holds between a material entity and a product that is generated through the intentional actions or functioning of the material entity

related_to.description: A relationship that is asserted between two named things

same_as.description: holds between two entities that are considered equivalent to each other

synonym.description: Alternate human-readable names for a thing

systematic_synonym.description: more commonly used for gene symbols in yeast

update_date.description: date on which thing was updated. This can be applied to nodes or edges

xenologous_to.description: a homology relationship characterized by an interspecies (horizontal) transfer since the common ancestor.

enabled_by.description: holds between a process and a physical entity, where the physical entity executes the process

has_input.description: holds between a process and a continuant, where the continuant is an input into the process

has_output.description: holds between a process and a continuant, where the continuant is an output of the process

has_participant.description: holds between a process and a continuant, where the continuant is somehow involved in the process

precedes.description: holds between two processes, where one completes before the other begins

Onset.description: The age group in which manifestations appear
Onset.title: Onset

OntologyClass.description: a concept or class in an ontology, vocabulary or thesaurus

subclass_of.description: holds between two classes where the domain class is a specialization of the range class

OntologyClass.title: OntologyClass

PairwiseGeneToGeneInteraction.description: An interaction between two genes or two gene products. May be physical (e.g. protein binding) or genetic (between genes). May be symmetric (e.g. protein interaction) or directed (e.g. phosphorylation)
PairwiseGeneToGeneInteraction.title: PairwiseGeneToGeneInteraction

PathognomonicityQuantifier.description: A relationship quantifier between a variant or symptom and a disease, which is high when the presence of the feature implies the existence of the disease
PathognomonicityQuantifier.title: PathognomonicityQuantifier

Phenomenon.description: a fact or situation that is observed to exist or happen, especially one whose cause or explanation is in question
Phenomenon.title: Phenomenon

PhenotypicSex.description: An attribute corresponding to the phenotypic sex of the individual, based upon the reproductive organs present.
PhenotypicSex.title: PhenotypicSex

PhysicalEntity.description: An entity that has physical properties such as mass, volume, or charge
PhysicalEntity.title: PhysicalEntity

PlanetaryEntity.description: Any entity or process that exists at the level of the whole planet
PlanetaryEntity.title: PlanetaryEntity

PopulationOfIndividualOrganisms.description: A collection of individuals from the same taxonomic class distinguished by one or more characteristics. Characteristics can include, but are not limited to, shared geographic location, genetics, phenotypes [Alliance for Genome Resources]

in_taxon.description: connects a thing to a class representing a taxon

PopulationOfIndividualOrganisms.title: PopulationOfIndividualOrganisms

PopulationToPopulationAssociation.description: An association between a two populations
PopulationToPopulationAssociation.title: PopulationToPopulationAssociation

Procedure.description: A series of actions conducted in a certain order or manner
Procedure.title: Procedure

Protein.description: A gene product that is composed of a chain of amino acid sequences and is produced by ribosome-mediated translation of mRNA
Protein.title: Protein

ProteinIsoform.description: Represents a protein that is a specific isoform of the canonical or reference protein. See https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4114032/
ProteinIsoform.title: ProteinIsoform

Provider.description: person, group, organization or project that provides a piece of information
Provider.title: Provider

Publication.description: Any published piece of information. Can refer to a whole publication, or to a part of it (e.g. a figure, figure legend, or section highlighted by NLP). The scope is intended to be general and include information published on the web as well as journals.
Publication.title: Publication

QuantityValue.description: A value of an attribute that is quantitative and measurable, expressed as a combination of a unit and a numeric value

has_numeric_value.description: connects a quantity value to a number

has_unit.description: connects a quantity value to a unit

QuantityValue.title: QuantityValue

RNAProductIsoform.description: Represents a protein that is a specific isoform of the canonical or reference RNA
RNAProductIsoform.title: RNAProductIsoform

RelationshipType.description: An OWL property used as an edge label
RelationshipType.title: RelationshipType

SequenceFeatureRelationship.description: For example, a particular exon is part of a particular transcript or gene
SequenceFeatureRelationship.title: SequenceFeatureRelationship

SequenceVariant.description: An allele that varies in its sequence from what is considered the reference allele at that locus.
SequenceVariant.title: SequenceVariant

SeverityValue.description: describes the severity of a phenotypic feature or disease
SeverityValue.title: SeverityValue

Transcript.description: An RNA synthesized on a DNA or RNA template by an RNA polymerase
Transcript.title: Transcript

TranscriptToGeneRelationship.description: A gene is a collection of transcripts
TranscriptToGeneRelationship.title: TranscriptToGeneRelationship

Treatment.description: A treatment is targeted at a disease or phenotype and may involve multiple drug 'exposures'

treats.description: holds between a therapeutic procedure or chemical substance and a disease or phenotypic feature that it is used to treat

Treatment.title: Treatment

VariantToPopulationAssociation.description: An association between a variant and a population, where the variant has particular frequency in the population

has_percentage.description: equivalent to has quotient multiplied by 100

VariantToPopulationAssociation.title: VariantToPopulationAssociation
